Last Updated: June 13, 2023

This document describes how we, as developers of the game "Sigma War: Fight against the Betas," collect, use, and share users' personal information.

Information Collection
To provide a better gaming experience, we collect certain information from users. This information may include, but is not limited to, the unique device ID, IP address, operating system version, and information regarding the use of the application.

Use of Information
We use the collected information to provide, maintain, improve, and develop our game. The collected information can also be used to customize the gaming experience for the user and for analytical purposes.

Sharing of Information
We do not share users' personal information with third parties, except for AdMob and other third-party services necessary for the operation of the application. AdMob may use the collected information to provide personalized advertising. For further details, please consult AdMob's privacy policy.

In-App Purchases
We offer in-app purchases in our game. These purchases are processed through the App Store's payment system. We do not have access to the user's payment or billing information.

Changes to the Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make significant changes to this policy, we will inform users through a notice within the game.

Contacts
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at the email address provided on the App Store.

By using our game, the user agrees to the collection and use of their information as described in this Privacy Policy.





